Clypeus With four setae located on the clypeal area; 1 + 1 anterior-lateral setae, posterior to the latter; and two central setae (
Fig. 13
). Clypeal area with very densely areolated surface (
Figs. 14, 15
).

Labrum . Mid-piece well developed and pigmented, with 8 sharp-pointed teeth. Side pieces with 13 + 12 filaments of different size (
Fig. 16
).

